 <purpose>
<p>This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module to record:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>a classification relationship between a class and a member;</p>
<note>In this part of ISO 10303, the term 'class' and 'set' are synonyms.</note>
</li>
<li><p>the specification of all the members of a class.</p></li>
</ul>
 </purpose>

 <inscope>
<li><p>a classification relationship between a class and a member;</p></li>
<li><p>the specification of all the members of class.</p></li>
</inscope>

 <outscope>
<li><p>relationships that are not classification relationships;</p></li>
<li><p>the existence of a class or set;</p></li>
<li><p>the distinction between a class or set that is defined by abstract criteria, and a class or set that is defined by enumerating its members;</p></li>
<li><p>the following set theory relationships:</p>
<ul>
<li>complement;</li>
<li>equivalence;</li>
<li>intersection;</li>
<li>power set;</li>
<li>proper subset;</li>
<li>subset;</li>
<li>union.</li>
</ul></li>
 </outscope>

